1. Pucaj iz pištolja i pogodi metak! (*metak* - noun in nominative case, meaning "bullet") (Shoot from the pistol and hit the bullet!)

2. Pretražili su mesto zločina i pronašli nekoliko metaka. (*metaka* - noun in genitive case, meaning "bullets") (They searched the crime scene and found several bullets.)

3. Policajci su videli odbačeni metak na ulici. (*metak* - noun in accusative case, meaning "bullet") (The policemen saw a discarded bullet on the street.)

4. Škripav zvuk metka je prekinuo tišinu u šumi. (*metka* - noun in genitive case, meaning "bullet") (The squeaking sound of the bullet broke the silence in the forest.)

5. Metak je prošao tik pored mene. (*metak* - noun in nominative case, meaning "bullet") (The bullet passed right by me.)

6. Trgovac je prodavao metke za lovačku pušku. (*metke* - noun in accusative case, meaning "bullets") (The merchant was selling bullets for a hunting rifle.)

7. Železnička stanica je bila meta napadača, koji je ispalio nekoliko metaka. (*metaka* - noun in genitive case, meaning "bullets") (The railway station was the target of the attacker, who fired several bullets.)

8. Uzmi metkove i napuni šaržer. (*metkove* - noun in accusative case, meaning "bullets") (Take the bullets and load the magazine.)

9. Metkovi su se razleteli na sve strane nakon eksplozije. (*metkovi* - noun in nominative plural form, meaning "bullets") (The bullets scattered everywhere after the explosion.)

10. U filmu su koristili prave metke za realističniji prikaz pucnjave. (*metke* - noun in accusative case, meaning "bullets") (They used real bullets in the movie for a more realistic portrayal of the shooting.)